# SSRF with Whitelist-Based Input Filter

## Executive Summary

The application was vulnerable to **Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)**. Although a hostname allowlist restricted requests to `stock.weliketoshop.net`, the validation could be bypassed by abusing URL parsing inconsistencies and double URL encoding.

The vulnerability allowed access to the internal administrative interface and execution of privileged functionality, resulting in the deletion of the user `carlos`.

---

# Vulnerability Information

**Category**

Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)

